Ihuoma Chiedozie, Abuja The newly appointed Postmaster General of the Federation and Chief Executive Officer of the Nigeria Postal Service, Dr Ismail Adewusi, has assumed duty at the agency’s headquarters in Abuja. A statement issued by General Manager, Corporate Communications, Mr Franklin Alao, said Adewusi resumed on Tuesday. In a maiden meeting he held with management and staff of NIPOST, Adewusi spoke of his intention to quickly harness the low hanging fruits to create an impact in his first 100 days in office. The statement disclosed that the Postmaster General promised to address challenges facing the agency, particularly infrastructural decay and low staff morale due to poor staff welfare. He also stressed the need to implement the Minister of Communications and Digital Economy’s directive on the use of POS for all transactions in all post offices in the country. Pantai had ordered the termination of cash transactions in NIPOST offices. Copyright PUNCH.
